Thanks for downloading migasfree client.

To install it, make sure you have these programs installed:

    * Python >= 3.6
    * python3-requests
    * python3-requests-toolbelt
    * python3-jwcrypto
    * python3-magic
    * python3-netifaces
    * python3-stdeb (to create a DEB package)
    * python3-cups
    * python3-rich
    * dmidecode
    * lshw >= 02.15

Then run these commands from the command prompt:

    $ cd bin
    $ ./create-package
    # <install package (deb or rpm)>

Or these commands if you are in Arch based distro:

    $ cd bin
    $ makepkg
    # <install package>

Or these commands to create a wheel Python package and install it:

    $ python3 setup.py bdist_wheel
    $ cd dist
    # pip3 install <generated_wheel_package>.whl

Check /etc/migasfree.conf configuration before run migasfree bin scripts.
If this file not exists, you can copy it from /usr/share/doc/migasfree-client/migasfree.conf.

And enjoy!

If you want execute 'migasfree sync' with some user, you can add this line in sudoers config:

    ALL ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/migasfree sync

If your migasfree server is configured over SSL, server certificate must be installed in system certificates.
